\begin_inset Formula $-cF^{\prime}(x)+cG^{\prime}(x)=u_{t}\!\left(0,x\right)=g\!\left(x\right)$
\end_inset

.
 De estas dos identidades obtenemos
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{multline*}
cf^{\prime}\!\left(x\right)+g\!\left(x\right)=2cG^{\prime}(x)\implies\\
\implies G(x)=\frac{1}{2c}\int_{0}^{x}cf^{\prime}\!\left(s\right)+g\!\left(s\right)\,ds=\frac{f\!\left(x\right)-f\!\left(0\right)}{2}+\frac{1}{2c}\int_{0}^{x}g\!\left(s\right)\,ds\implies\\
